verbose_text: Furthermore, TNFR2 signaling through the non canonical NF-kappaB pathway is induced by TNF-alpha in ILC2s, and selective blocking of NF-kappaB-inducing kinase (NIK) inhibits the development of ILC2 dependent AHR.
evidence: TNFR2 signaling through the non-canonical NF-kappaB pathway is induced by TNF-alpha
